text: my mother frequently commented to me about how unusually empathetic i could be. i always sensed she was puzzled by this part of me. not judging, but also not relating to my vulnerability for others whom i sensed to be in need or distress.  as a child, i did not realize that everyone was not wired that way.  my ability to sense heightened tensions and to ask about them caused much trouble.  asking someone what is wrong when the only measures of strength and perfection are in â€”no display of difficult or non-positive feelings, was unwelcomeâ€”resented.  i was the feeler.  i felt it all. and i dared to speak of it. i have cautioned my boys that the quickest way to agitate their father, my sister, or anyone in their â€œfamiliesâ€ is to ask â€œwhatâ€™s wrong? are you ok?â€ those ironically and consistently turned out to be fight starters, followed by confusing and painful distance and silence.  those inquiries are treated as trouble making. #empath #empathy #empathetic #metoo #ihearyou #iseeyou #connection #compassion #holdspace #brenebrown #stonewall #silenttreatment #scapegoat #blacksheep #narcissist

tonight we will celebrate black filmmakers and actors.....meet @johniseeee "peezoo" bowie from the "quiet and clear" movie by executive producer @andreverdunjones as we feature the movies trailer as well as other selections. ***message from the director***
in october 2017, the same month #metoo went viral, Â andre verdun jones â€“ co-founder of the black lgbtq publication the tenth magazineÂ and executive producer of award winning short film mr. okra â€“ invited me to his hometown of franklin, louisiana after seeing my experimental short film dixieland (filmed in new orleans). jones encouraged me to expand on its themes in a short film. 
upon arriving in franklin, intersectional feminism was quickly becoming a talking point online and i was curious about its reach in louisiana. as a queerÂ filmmaker of color, i naturallyÂ gravitateÂ towards spotlighting stories of minority groups. 
making a short film that investigated gender inequality and sexual assault in this region, and that centered on the black, female body, posed a number of challenges. historically, film has revealed a white-centered perspective even while depicting the black body. i employed impressionistic principles to reflect the full interior life of the all-black cast and to implode tropes of black communities in the rural south.

of equal importance was representing franklin, louisiana with sublime images of black life; to reclaim its sweeping landscapes as a home of black america; to paint the deep south with light, shadow and darkness as a place for black celebration and struggle. --andre rangiah, director

for three years, waterbury danced up to 36 hours a week, graduating with an offer to turn pro. today, her professional dance career is over. trenell:
trenell eaton, is a woman of god first and a superhero mother to her son.  born and partially raised in the district of columbia, trenell developed a resilience to her childhood traumas. despite her shortcomings, she was able to overcome the adversity of having survived multiple episodes of homelessness, abuse, and poverty.  instead of falling victim to statistical outcomes she decided that she would use her plights to build a platform for herself and women and girls just like her across the world.

trenell earned a bachelor's degree in sociology from morgan state university and is completing her masters of jurisprudence in child law and policy at loyola university of chicago school of law.  currently she manages special education schools for the dc public schools and serves as an advocate for children in her community.  in addition, trenell is the founder of the non-profit organization i am beautiful because, a womanâ€™s awareness organization that supports women and girls who have been victims of child sexual abuse.  this is seed that was planted from her own person experience with child sexual abuse. "i needed a hero so, i became one"

loving who we are in the mist of overcoming will help us smile more, love more and eventually thrive through. . 
healing is not a race, but the work allows us to become stronger, in love and permits us to laugh more. .

long post: now that the cat's out of the bag, i will share my journey! i would like to thank the florida international pageants for selecting me to compete as mrs. n. florida 2019!! this year's pageant will be exactly 20 years from the date i first competed in the international system! ğŸ˜³ğŸ¤© i love pageantry, but i almost didn't want to share my journey this time on insta/fb. you see, some people don't know what you have gone through and tend to judge you, not knowing all of your reasons why.

growing up i was an extremely shy and withdrawn child. being molested as a child by distant family members left me feeling ugly, with little self-worth. it took me a long time and a lot of prayer to come to the realization that it was not my fault and that i was worthy. i am still getting better in some of those areas. reaching out and helping others has been my saving grace. there's just something about when you concentrate on others needs, it fills you with such a joy and helped me to get through the rough spots.

for my entire life, i have known that i was meant to be of service to others.  there is no greater way to challenge ones self, than to put yourself in a situation where you can absolutely do good for another human being, with no expectations.  this has also been my driving force for when i compete in pageantry because i am afforded more opportunities to make a positive difference in others lives.  it is not my time yet to hang up my glass slippers, because my work is not done and although i do not need a crown, sash or a title, these same three items have a way of pushing open doors to the hearts of others by changing lives, so with that being said, come along with me on my newest adventure, as i prepare to compete for the title of mrs. florida international 2019! 
follow my journey, as i continue my personal legacy to continue to change lives through my "dare to be me- youth empowerment" program!
.
.
#internationalpageants #iamenough #endchildabuse #stopsexualabuse #pageantry #metoo #mrsflorida #thesisterhoodisstrong #nevergiveup#d2bm #pageantry #swimsuit#mrsfloridainternational#momof5#aerobicwear
 #mrsintl2019 #mrsflint #thesisterhoodisstrong

text:
it doesn't matter what day it is... you have the opportunity to make the change that you have been wanting to. it's baby steps to become the person that you want to become and with each step you are changing your life.

what's one thing that you could do today to move towards the person you want to be? for me, i'm going to do self care and relax. this is something i struggle with so it's baby steps to figure out how to best make doing nothing for a day serve me.

now i, of course, have no idea if that is what @taylorswift meant when she wrote those lyrics for her song, â€œso it goesâ€, but that is my interpretation.  i find them to be liberating and representation of a strong woman who believes in herself.  can you relate to these lyrics? ğŸ’œ

venus & pluto catch up at 22 degrees capricorn, with saturn 5 degrees away at 17 capricorn. expect ancient angst or unresolved issues from past power imbalances to be reactivated so they can be properly resolved.

venus represents personal self-worth, whom you attract & relate to. pluto represents repression, temptation(s), perceptions & explosive repercussions. at 22 capricorn, they activate the sabian symbol of transforming setbacks with grace of spirit and self-discipline. 
real power comes not from winning everything, but from level-headed practicality; sometimes the feelings of a situation are more important than the event itself. to learn from experience, be loyal to long range ends and fight irresponsible acceptance of the worst. 
saturn encourages us to cope, and come to terms with constraints; in capricorn it exalts peaceful communitiesâ€™ stability and responsible leadership. sounds like the #metoo nuns movement and likely the lgbtqai+ are not going to abate any time soon. could they even join forces? time will tell.

this configuration point at 14th september, which promises to be an interesting point in time as the themes of ancestral values, motherhood and how the â€˜sins of the fathersâ€™ got passed down will be highlighted, as well as what we can potentially become while the next generation defines who they are and what they stand for.

daily mantra: â€œi refine my identity and the reality i create every time i clearly see what values and ideals i stand up for. as i find patterns and try new angles, great changes happen.â€ #gamechanger #wellbeing #positivevibes #emotions #astrology #healing #innerpeace #change

https://twitter.com/iansmadrig/status/1068605537246425088?s=21
now that billionaire child sex trafficker jeffrey epstein is back in the news, it seems like a good time to take a closer look at allegations that donald trump raped a 13-year-old girl at epstein's manhattan home in 1994.

trump is more than overdue for his #metooâ  â   reckoning.
important caveat: i am an activist and an attorney, not a journalist. i strongly encourage journalists to explore this further. 
these claims got little attention because the accuser has remained anonymous. but new details uncovered by @miamiherald on epstein bolster her story.
â€œjane doeâ€ alleges donald trump sexually assaulted her on four separate occasions, culminating in a rape when she was just 13 at jeffrey epsteinâ€™s mansion. 
her evidence? three sworn declarations â€“ from her, a friend she confided in at the time, and one of epsteinâ€™s recruiters.
this case was filed in new york federal court in 2016. you can read her pleading here: politico.com/f/?id=00000158â€¦

the case was not dismissed. jane withdrew her complaint on november 4, 2016, saying she was â€œafraid to show her faceâ€ due to â€œnumerous threatsâ€ against her.
jane came to new york in june 1994 â€œin the hope of starting a modeling career.â€ she soon met "tiffany," who offered to bring her to parties where she could meet folks in the business - hosted by epstein.

this is eerily similar to tales of recruiters in @miamiherald's reporting.
jane claims trump had â€œsexual contact" with her at four parties she attended that summer. she understood both trump and epstein "knew that [she] was 13 years old.â€ the fourth time, she says "trump tied me to a bed, exposed himself to me, and then proceeded to forcibly rape me."
jane claims a 12-year-old named maria was forced to be involved in the third encounter. she never saw maria again after that.

following the rape, jane says trump threatened to hurt her and her family if she ever told anyone. he suggested he could make her â€œdisappear like maria.â€
jane is not the only witness offered in this filing. a woman using the pseudonym

text:
those feminine hormones that help to bestow the miracle of reproduction on women may ironically make them more susceptible to addiction. 
the latest entry in a series of studies from vanderbilt universityâ€™s pharmacology department shows that, when a femaleâ€™s estrogen is peaking, she learns faster, craves adventure and novel experiences, is more likely to seek romance whether good or bad, and is more prone to seek rewards.  that makes her more likely to fall prey to addiction.

the investigators had previously demonstrated that higher estrogen levels intensify the brainâ€™s dopamine reward release following cocaine use.  these latest experiments employed a rat model to show that females, in the presence of a light trigger, were more motivated than males to do what it takes to repeatedly get a dose of cocaine.  female hormones facilitate repeated drug ingestion.

those of us who applaud the #metoo movement see this type of information as a tool for liberating women from the restrictions of their biology.  knowing that women may become addicted to drugs more readily mid-cycle, their doctors should be particularly careful to avoid narcotic use during these times and probably anytime.

women themselves should also use this intelligence about the impact of their hormonal cycles to plan their work and play schedules to take advantage of the benefits of their estrogen peaks while avoiding its pitfalls.

estrogens, addiction, menstrualcycle, healthnews, healthtips
#estrogens #addiction #menstrualcycle #healthnews #healthtips

arts in town | in the age of social identity politics world-wide shifting from inclusion to division, the recent d&g scandal on the chinese people, the #metoo movement etc, the need to dismantle discrimination barriers continue to dominate the headlines. the role of an artist and of a gallery is not to enjoy the splendid isolation outside of this mainstream conversation, but to channel, amplify and dissect the issues that drive it. artists themselves, both male and female, will respond to the debate in their own way. as art synthesizes and distills the news cacophony into its essential note, the result, we believe, will be a message of unity rather than division.
.
anticipation | now - 2 mar | galerie ora-ora
.

i thought i was broken. â €
i thought there was something wrong with me that could never be fixed.â €
.â €
i would watch people with happy partners, happy kids, happy family - looking relaxed - and think... why not me?â €
.
to others i looked successful, and in many ways i really was. yet i suffered quietly from bouts of anxiety and depression on and off for years. but i wouldn't let it beat me! i always did my best to overcome my difficulties, and often hid my fears.â €
.
i have read 100s of books, attended countless seminars and sat in many a therapists office - just trying to feel 'normal' to feel like i 'belong' to feel like i am 'enough'.â €
.â €
i trained in non conventional healing techniques that quickly push the needle to happiness, without having to talk about my experience over and over again.â €
.â €
now, i want to share with you some of the easiest, and best ways to get your life on track and quickly move from abuse to abundance.â €
.â €
this book has already gone to #1 best seller internationally. no big publisher, no big marketing team. just me, on a mission to move us from abuse to abundance.â €
.â €
it's for any adult survivors of abuse, and it will help you:â €
.â €
- understand why you've been stuckâ €
- move the one big thing that blocks your happinessâ €
- know how to have difficult conversations with the ones you love to help them understand your needsâ €
- understand why you're stuck in a loop with money, love or self confidenceâ €
.â €
and importantly... move towards the abundant life you deserve.â €
.

.â €

text: i'm honestly mad as hell. went to a bar tonight i've never been to and the doorman kissed the girl before me and then came and kissed me half on the mouth, half on the cheek. before asking us the $10 entry fee and after asking for our ids. watched him do it to the girl behind me too. tried to say something to the girl in front of me and she brushed me off because she knew him and was used to this shit. anyway i got a drink at the bar since i paid $10 to get in and i told the bar owner, in honestly the politest way--not trying to start trouble if i can help it--to please tell his doorman to stop kissing girls on their way in. he thanked me and then never left his place behind the bar to talk to dude. anyway, long story short, i clocked that motherfucker in the head with the nasty side of my wrist brace on my way out after trying to explain to him (and his female fiancÃ©e) why that wasn't ok and getting nowhere but belittled and gaslighted. fuck that shit yo, i'm not here for it. terrible end to a terrible week, absolutely will never be going there again. âœŒï¸ #assault #tw #cw #harassment #compliance #banned #barnightmares #ptsd #cptsd #mi #metoo #carpaltunnel #chronicillness #chronicpain #why #canijustdrinkinpeace

text: everyone can agree that no one knows everything. everyone is at different levels of how much information they have absorbed. everyone can agree that some people devote a lot of their time to really understand something or â€œspecializeâ€ in a particular subject or topic. and even within the same subject people may still not fully agree with one another but we can all agree that we can disagree about what is important to us and what we want to absorb can be different than what others may want to absorb. for example i may want to absorb information about science while my brother like to absorb knowledge of insects. everyone can agree that we are all different and are interested in different things. we can all agree that a form of learning and absorbing information is through others. an example would be a mother can demonstrate to her daughter how to hold her first newborn since the mother she has prior experience. (her experience may or may not be the best but itâ€™s still experience that her daughter never had) its up to how the daughter listens,acts and interprets the information that will influence her decision into how she will use the information that was given to her. she may or may not accept and absorb the information and that is her choice. we can all agree that not all of us on earth have the freedom to make choices the way we would like. but we are all constantly absorbing information and constantly learning from our own experience and that of others. that is why who is around you is a key aspect of the opportunity and availability of information you will be exposed to. if you look around you, are there people who are fueling your mind with opportunities and other things you are genuinely interested in to order to give you better understanding of something? we can all agree that we can all find ourselves confused at times because of information overload and we need more time or experience to really register what is going on or has happened. we can all agree that some people may need more time than others to absorb information. we can all agree that many of us are in different positions in life with different situations both negative or positive or minor..ğŸ‘‡

text:
yesterday, was my first experience ever in attending theatre show; medosa. 
from what i have read and been told, medosa is a greek myth that describes a monstrous women. anyway, i felt the myth itself was complicated but from what i gathered, medosa was a woman full of anger and rage but wasn't as monstrous as the myth describes. 
rebellion women were always described as outrageous , sinners, bad and shameful. they were suppressed and were used as an example to scare the rest of women tribe to not dare and do the same. 
the show was very emotional and it got me into tears especially when one women trapped another women and then rapped her head with a rope and kept shouting at her. i could relate to this very scene. 
women in some of our societies are still seen as an object. women are still expected to be no more than housewives, no more than a shadow of a man in politics, work and universities. i'm not belittling those who are housewives at all. i'm talking about all the choices that have been made for us, chosen for us, written for us. 
there was a scene in which a man tried to talk over a group of women and he was standing alone in the middle, they stood together and he couldn't finish a sentence. that says alot. i strongly recommend the show. 
#meduso #jasminvardimon #theater #shrewsbury #womenrights #feminism #politics #workplace #feminist #feministart #empoweringwomen #strongwomen #standtogether #unwomenuk #unwomen #firstexperience #standtogether #sayno #bemore #equality #severntheater #metoo

text:
christopher wylie, who worked with a cambridge university academic to obtain the data, told the observer: â€œwe exploited facebook to harvest millions of peopleâ€™s profiles. and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.â€ documents seen by the observer, and confirmed by a facebook statement, show that by late 2015 the company had found out that information had been harvested on an unprecedented scale. however, at the time it failed to alert users and took only limited steps to recover and secure the private information of more than 50 million individuals.

the data was collected through an app called thisisyourdigitallife, built by academic aleksandr kogan, separately from his work at cambridge university. through his company global science research (gsr), in collaboration with cambridge analytica, hundreds of thousands of users were paid to take a personality test and agreed to have their data collected for academic use.

however, the app also collected the information of the test-takersâ€™ facebook friends, leading to the accumulation of a data pool tens of millions-strong. facebookâ€™s â€œplatform policyâ€ allowed only collection of friendsâ€™ data to improve user experience in the app and barred it being sold on or used for advertising. the discovery of the unprecedented data harvesting, and the use to which it was put, raises urgent new questions about facebookâ€™s role in targeting voters in the us presidential election. it comes only weeks after indictments of 13 russians by the special counsel robert mueller which stated they had used the platform to perpetrate â€œinformation warfareâ€ against the us.

carole cadwalladr & emma graham-harrison
the guardian

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer".
.
in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field."
.
despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaignâ€™s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of peopleâ€™s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there â€œcould have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheatingâ€. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesdayâ€™s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

footage of nigel farage swigging a pint and thanking steve bannon and breitbart for the brexit result was deleted from a breitbart youtube channel, following the data scandal surrounding cambridge analytica.
.
- well done bannon, well done breitbart, the ex-ukip leader announces in the short clip. - you helped with this. hugely.

farageâ€™s nod to steve bannon certainly hasnâ€™t aged well in the context of the recent storm around cambridge analyticaâ€™s influence over the eu referendum.

it was revealed that data from 50 million facebook profiles were looked at against the electoral register, and then used to build an algorithm which analyses peopleâ€™s personality traits in relation to their voting behaviour.

this data could then be used to find potential swing voters and create messages tailored to influence them politically.

the firmâ€™s vice president at the time was steve bannon, who was also head of the right-wing website breitbart and was running donald trumpâ€™s campaign to become us president.

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer".
.
in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field."
.
despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text_retweet:
#reposting my first post because it is so important to recognize the signs before itâ€™s too late. behavior like this isnâ€™t healthy. couples have ups and downs, yes, but just because someone says they love you, doesnâ€™t mean they respect you or your boundaries. abuse isnâ€™t love. #staysafe and #wakeup. abusers of all kind are in no way excused, no matter what. when it comes down to it, they just want power. thereâ€™s so much music glorifying violence and even murder, but really, violent and abusive actions and words are those of someone who is extremely afraid. all acts of abuse are just a way to feel powerful, to feel like you matter, as if the dominance you feel hurting someone gives you meaning. aggression and intimidation are just tactics to feel important, to stay relevant in someoneâ€™s mind and feel high knowing it. because unfortunately, since the dawn of time, it seems, people who feel feared, who see others cower at their feet, feel it translates to respect. but thatâ€™s the furthest thing from it. fear does not equal respect. it never has, and never will. fear is fear. violence is violence, abuse is abuse, and nothing more. it is an ignorance, an inability to respond rather than react. it is an all consuming, self serving priority for power and greed that stems, ultimately, like all acts of hatred do, from ones own deep self loathing.
.
.

.
.
here we are now, still together. miraculously together. holding each other within an inch of the cliff. .
.
.
i realise now that you were screaming too. you too were broken, emptied, filled with pain. we were both betrayed.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text_retweet:
reposted from @persatuanburuh -  #repost @jaringanmuda(@repost_via_instant)yuk kita berani melawan pelaku pelecehan!
â€¢

jika memungkinkan untuk kamu berani merespon cepat pelaku pelecehan, ada beberapa tips untuk melawan tindak pelecehan:

jangan diam: tunjukkan ketidaksukaan kita terhadap tindakan yang melecehkan, bisa dengan teriak, melotot, membentak atau mendatangi pelaku dan sampaikan
ketidaksukaan kita. hal itu juga bisa menjadi sarana penyadaran bagi pelaku, bahwa tindakannya itu melecehkan. jika tidak memungkinkan, kamu bisa berlari menjauhi pelaku dan menceritakannya pada orang lain.

ketika di kampus, seringkali kita beraktivitas hingga malam hari, sehingga ketika pulang, jalanan atau gang sudah sepi. untuk berjaga-jaga kita dapat membawa peluit, semprotan cabe, atau semprotan lain seperti parfum.

jika terjadi tindakan seperti dihadang ditengah jalan atau dipeluk paksa secara tiba-tiba kita dapat merespon dengan menyemprotkan semprotan cabe/parfum ke mata pelaku, meniup peluit untuk meminta pertolongan, pukul, tendang ataupun serang balik pelaku dengan barang bawaan kita (tas, sepatu, buku dsb). â€¢

bollywood also needs wcc, feels deepika padukone

bollywood actor deepika padukone said that women in cinema collection which was formed in malayalam cinema can be introduced in bollywood too.
she said there are good men in the film industry. women should not become anti-men. these discussions must not isolate men. the endeavours for gender justice was not efficient. it has a long way to go. #metoo movement became stronger out of the blue. but, it is hard to change many things which are prevalent in the society. she was talking to journalist anuradha sengupta here at the international advertising association world congress on friday.

text_retweet:
reposted from @persatuanburuh -  #repost @jaringanmuda(@repost_via_instant)yuk kita berani melawan pelaku pelecehan!
â€¢

jika memungkinkan untuk kamu berani merespon cepat pelaku pelecehan, ada beberapa tips untuk melawan tindak pelecehan:

jangan diam: tunjukkan ketidaksukaan kita terhadap tindakan yang melecehkan, bisa dengan teriak, melotot, membentak atau mendatangi pelaku dan sampaikan
ketidaksukaan kita. hal itu juga bisa menjadi sarana penyadaran bagi pelaku, bahwa tindakannya itu melecehkan. jika tidak memungkinkan, kamu bisa berlari menjauhi pelaku dan menceritakannya pada orang lain.

ketika di kampus, seringkali kita beraktivitas hingga malam hari, sehingga ketika pulang, jalanan atau gang sudah sepi. untuk berjaga-jaga kita dapat membawa peluit, semprotan cabe, atau semprotan lain seperti parfum.

jika terjadi tindakan seperti dihadang ditengah jalan atau dipeluk paksa secara tiba-tiba kita dapat merespon dengan menyemprotkan semprotan cabe/parfum ke mata pelaku, meniup peluit untuk meminta pertolongan, pukul, tendang ataupun serang balik pelaku dengan barang bawaan kita (tas, sepatu, buku dsb). â€¢

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - iâ€™ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now iâ€™m about to go back, knowing what i know, and weâ€™re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trumpâ€™s election, trumpeted the return of their â€œpopulist heroâ€ on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publicationâ€™s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
abortion, lets talk about it.

so can we first talk about how both parties choose to refer to both of their positions in terms of abortion? republicans call it â€œpro-lifeâ€ while democrats call it â€œpro-choiceâ€ â€¦ like ok??? both sound as if theyâ€™re trying to protect the rights of someone else, but imagine if the democratic partyâ€™s â€œpro-choiceâ€ stance was referred to as â€œpro-deathâ€ and the republican partyâ€™s stance was referred to as â€œanti-womenâ€™s rightsâ€, how would you feel? letâ€™s decide, together.

pro-life? 
well of course i would love to protect the lives of someone whose life may be taken away from them without their own say in the matter.Â Â just because someone is growing in someone else, doesnâ€™t mean theyâ€™re not alive.Â Â weâ€™re all growing in some way, shape, or form, so why are we allowed to dismiss a life based solely on a stage of life, just because its early? does that not infringe on human rights?

pro-choice?
while pro-choice argues that a woman is entitled to do with her body whatever she wants because its her body, no one elseâ€™s. who on earth could argue with that.Â Â this is a completely valid argument.Â Â so if there is extra tissue growing in her body that she does not want, why should she not be allowed to get rid of it?Â Â why is it anyone elseâ€™s business, especially the government? does that not infringe on human rights?

so whatâ€™s the right answer to such a debated question? thatâ€™s why its an issue. no one knows the right answer to this question, and that is exactly why itâ€™s an issue.Â Â as a gay man, i feel as though i am in no place to deny a womanâ€™s right to her body.Â Â if she feels there is something in her body that needs to be removed, it is her ~god given right~ to go to a doctor and have it removed.

so this is how i feel as a gay man, the creation of life is the most beautiful thing in the entire world.Â Â it is what made you today, and arenâ€™t you glad youâ€™re here with us today?Â Â ok,Â Â so like i donâ€™t have a boyfriend, but even if i did, we could not physically give the gift of life that women can give without artificial help from doctors.Â Â that is a gift that i wish i could give so bad.Â Â it is so beautiful. #trump #republican #democrat #america

text:
march 23, 2019: rahuâ€™s returning to gemini, & big changes are coming.

https://t.co/pdj3aih84z

on march 23rd we are going to experience a new shift, with the lunar nodes returning to the â€œgemini/sagittariusâ€ axis. this is a transformative section of the skyâ€”the last time the nodes were here we had the 2000 presidential election, which was one of the most consequential elections in history, followed by the 9/11 terrorist event. (i break this down in extensive detail during my free webinar, here.) the leading edge of the nodal axis, called rahu, typically shows the â€œtip of the spear.â€ itâ€™s quite remarkable to look back at the last three rahu cycles and notice the focal points of these periods, especially culturally. these placements are based on vedic astrology which has always used a sidereal-based zodiac, accurate with the fixed space, not western astrology which uses the seasons to calculate the zodiac.

january 2016 â€“ september 2017:
rahu in leo showed the rise of nationalism and â€œstrongmen leadersâ€ around the world. think of brexit, trump, putin, erdogan, xi, and the weakening of alliances such as nato.

september 2017 â€“ march 2019:
rahu in cancer showed a resurgence in the divine feminine and respect for women. think of the #metoo movement, womenâ€™s rights being at the forefront of societal issues, and the recent â€œblue waveâ€ cluster of female congresswomen in u.s.

march 23 2019 â€“ september 2020:
rahu entering gemini will show a focus on learning new things and getting better information, data, and communication. many challenges to our beliefs and preconceptions will be at the forefront.

yes we have developed way ahead of time on the technology front and that's has brought us to a start of a digital era,  however along with that it has brought across a wrong thinking process (adjustment living) , we have started to set our lifestyle based on the western culture but adapting and adjusting it to our own requirements,  in return it has caused undue troubles rather than betterment,  however there are a few who have taken advantage of the situation i mean to say men and women alike,  for their own benefit,  have seen a few with my own eyes,  who have taken advantage of the boys and left them high and dry and troubled those guys for their own benefit,. and vice versa guys.  however please b aware of these unwanted elements and keep away from such intimate information on social media... it's. just a few clicks and it's out.

text:
in â€˜glass ceiling (nz aotearoa)â€™ multiple colours and shapes are seen closeup among 200 million shards of shattered glass, diversity in a sea of white. the 16.5 tonne mass fills the floor, creeps up the silo walls and pushes back against transparent thresholds at three arched doorways. the metaphoric glass ceiling transforms from an invisible planar barrier above to become substrate and structure, palpable and present, liberating and inspiring, yet access remains problematic and restricted.
.
.
.

text:
in the time of the #metoo and #timesup movement, international bestselling author and leading global expert on mental strength amy morin turns her focus to feminism, explaining what it meansâ€”and what it takesâ€”to be a mentally strong woman.

the emergence of the #metoo and #timesup movements have awakened society and encouraged women to find their voice and claim their power. but to do this, women must learn to improve their own mental strength. contending with a host of difficult issuesâ€”from sexual assault on college campuses, to equal pay and pay gaps, to mastering different negotiation stylesâ€”demands psychological toughness. in this crucial book, prominent psychotherapist and licensed clinical social worker amy morin gives women the techniques to build mental muscleâ€”and just as important, she teaches them what not to do.

text:
masuk ke dalam topik pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja, kevin memiliki pandangan menarik mengenai permasalahan ini. kevin mengemukakan bahwa secara general terdapat perbedaan pandangan dari orang-orang yang tidak menyadari bahwa perilakunya termasuk suatu bentuk pelecehan seksual. pendidikan dan sosialisasi pada usia dini sangat mempengaruhi bagaimana seseorang berinteraksi. di saat kebanyakan anak perempuan diajarkan untuk menjaga perilaku dan cara berpakaian untuk menghindari pelecehan seksual, kebanyakan anak laki-laki justru dididik untuk menjadi â€œpenaklukâ€. hal-hal seperti ini menyebabkan pola pikir yang salah, yakni pelecehan seksual terjadi karena perilaku dan gaya berpakaian korban. disisi lain, ketika laki-laki dewasa menggoda perempuan, sering dianggap sukses menunjukkan suatu ciri maskulinitasnya.
.
"pandangan untuk perempuan sebagai objek seksual yang malu-malu tapi mau harus dilawan dengan kencang. karena pandangan itu yang menyulitkan untuk mempercayai korban pelecehan seksual.â€
.
#sayneverokay #neverokayproject #metoo #gerakbersama

text:
"because narcissists can`t derive self-worth from within, they stay chronically dissatisfied. like a cup with a hole in it - nobody could ever fill them up. nacrs are dissatisfied with themselves, so they seek an ego boost from others, but it`s never enough. even while in the throes of "love-bombing" with their latest "soulmate"/victim, narcissists are secretly scanning for alternatives, and in the back if the narc's mind lingers the question: "what else is out there? is there anyone else who could make me feel better about myself?""

text:
ğŸŒ• watching this time lapse makes me feel the most uncomfortable. so here goes. ğŸŒ self-care, self-love, self-worth... to cultivate these practices takes a lot of space, attention, emotional & physical energy, and commitment. but holy shit, is it worth it... the pain of sitting with grief, carving a knife into wounds so old i was convinced they werenâ€™t really wounds, but now iâ€™ve opened them to see just how strong and capable i am. and wow itâ€™s a lot.
ğŸŒ• iâ€™ve learned that in the midst of my pain, i also feel joy. i feel relief, clarity, recognition when i allow my pain to be, when i express myself fully and donâ€™t protect others from my feelings. in case you didnâ€™t know, all of your feelings matter. including the ones that hurt. and especially the ones that others try to tell you are wrong or donâ€™t matter!! iâ€™ve been traumatized and shut down for too long, but iâ€™m tired of hiding from myself, from the world. and so, i will no longer hide. for my own sake - for myself and for no one else - i will be. ğŸŒ‘ three men have sexually abused me in my life. people i trusted werenâ€™t there when i needed them the most. and although itâ€™s true that none of this defines me, that defense, which iâ€™ve put up for so long, no longer serves me. it doesnâ€™t soothe the pain or make what they did to me any less fucked up. it doesnâ€™t acknowledge the overwhelming fear, hate, anxiety, and anger iâ€™ve developed. it doesnâ€™t make up for the fact that i began to distrust the world at only four years old, and that now trust, especially in myself, is far from easy. my past has consumed me in ways i never knew it could. and itâ€™s so fucking sad that this happened to me, and that it happens to so many people. and that i may never get the apologies i deserve. and i know that i deserve better, and that i am not broken because of my broken family. iâ€™m thankful for the space iâ€™ve had to open up my wounds and to share. i am stronger because of it. i am strong, i am worth it, and i am so, so grateful for the people who have shown and continue to show me unconditional love, because we all deserve to feel loved. thank you for reading. i love you. you are amazing.

one word to my abuser, never ever call me a "cunt" again. i am the mother of your three children and i demand respect. #metoo

text:
this time 2 years ago i was sitting in an investigative office.
.
i felt sick to my stomach as i shared the address of where i was raped. i explained that more then 6 people did nothing to help me, but instead- mocked me and created a safe space for my abuser. i completely down played the forced encounter that occurred almost immediately prior to that 25 year old man kicking my world off its axis. to this day- i still donâ€™t even consider it part of my abuse history.
.
this wasnâ€™t an attack- it was a plan.
.
as i sat reliving the harrowing details: describing how the night unfolded it was clear even my advocate was not comfortable.
how do monsters like this exist? and how did a young newly 16 year old girl find them?
.
i wasnâ€™t brave then.
i didnâ€™t want to share my story- i didnâ€™t even want to remember it, but i did every single day.
i still do. .
his face- her smirk, their laughs, the smell of southern comfort, the feeling of betrayal from a best friend and the dark, twisted, denial that followed: its burned into me forever. itâ€™s a permanent mark.
.
but every single mark on my skin, every single experience these eyes have seen, every single touch and iâ€™ve felt- is me.
.
that was one day of my life.
.
my skin holds scars of my motherhood. my eyes have seen the world, the fireworks, the stars, and the sea. my body has felt the warmth of my children, my family, and a real man who wants to see me smile and win.
.
transform 20 wasnâ€™t just a workout.

text:
your body
your body is yours
to protect & to defend
your absolute right
â€¦
note: self-defense can be physical or verbal. this poem is part of a series, and i am working on a fuller version. i hope any bit is helpful to those who may be abused, attacked, harassed, bullied, etc. or those who want to prevent that.

escaping the bear

text:
nobody had a perfect childhood. we all experience trauma in one form or another while we grow up. it is during those times that we develop the foundation for how we respond to our feelings as adults. i didn't realize how important it is to get in touch with my inner child and understand why i feel or react the way i do to things until i started processing my trauma in therapy.
.
.
.
i look at this picture and i just want to pick up that little girl and give her a huge hug. i want to tell her how brave she is and that eventually she will be able to make the choice to walk away. i want to tell her that it is okay not to be okay. i want to tell her that her feelings matter and she has every right to feel her feels. i want to tell her to stop waiting to be saved, because there is no knight in shining armor. i want to tell her she has the courage and the strength to save herself, even more so i want to tell her that she will.
.
.
.
through meditation with my inner child i have begun to understand why, when my feelings are too big or too scary, i respond the way i do. in those moments, where my feelings are too intense, i have to take a minute and get in touch with my breath. i check in with my inner child to remind her that we are safe now. i thank her for protecting us so well growing up, and tell her that now it is my turn.
.
.
.
#innerchild #selfcare #meditation #selfcompassion #selflove #emotionalwellbeing #survivor #takebackcontrol #findyourvoice #useyourvoice #courage #bravery #emotionalabuse #itsokaynottobeokay #choice #selfaware #selfawareness #metoo

text:
jan 2018 vs feb 2019

so when i took the new photos today, by disdain was real. i picked at every roll, i got annoyed with wobbling skin, and i was frustrated with how my clothes fit. so what did i do? i left the photos alone, i walked away from the mirror and i told myself that i am beautiful regardless. that these things do not define me and i have worked so hard. to get to where i am that i refuse to let one moment shatter me. i was beautiful in january of last year, and i'm beautiful now. i decided to change to healthy habits. this was never solely supposed to be about losing weight. that defeats the purpose of body positivity. my body is perfect the way it is and i'm doing good to try and treat it well. my well being matters more than the number on the scale. as long as i'm watching out for my mental, physical and emotional health i know i will be okay. i am amazing.

#loveyourself #metoo #mentalhealth #physicalhealth #emotionalhealth #imatter #imbeautiful #curvygirls

text:
being spiritually advanced does not always mean being good to your family + friends + lovers + community. nor does it mean you are aware of boundaries and basic healthy socio-political safety and beliefs. these are things we must learn or in some cases its about things we need to unlearn. its really disheartening and confusing to realize this but also necessary for my emotional and mental safety (and sometimes our physical safety as well as we can see with monks, priests, yogis and pandits who are predators, narcissists, abusive etc ). people who can have extremely psychic abilities does not automatically mean they will be kind to you. 
in hindu myths we learn that even demons can pray to the gods and the gods will grant them boons. if you are diligent and devoted to your prayer you will be rewarded in that realm. but you may still be a asshole on earth. so... what now? and thats not gods fault. gods are not always benevolent nurturers sometimes they are just working in arts of energy not interpersonal interactions. drawing the energy down into this earth in our human bodies while being aware of our treatment of our loved ones can be a useful tool. status and advancement spiritually is great but are you still an ass?

in hindu myths we learn that even demons can pray to the gods and the gods will grant them boons. if you are diligent and devoted to your prayer you will be rewarded in that realm. but you may still be a asshole on eah. so... what now? and thats not gods fault. gods are not always benevolent nuurers sometimes they are just working in as of energy not interpersonal interactions. drawing the energy down into this eah in our human bodies while being aware of our treatment of our loved ones can be a useful tool. status and advancement spiritually is great but are you still an ass?

the charges come just a week after a video surfaced of the singer allegedly #sexually assaulting an #underage girl.
the 52-year-old performer is accused of sexually abusing four #victims, according to #court records.
nine of the counts specify that the victim was between 13 and 16. one count did not specify any age. in the case in which the victim was not identified as a minor, the singer is accused of forcing #sexualcontact on the victim by use of force or the threat of force.

 so small,

dictating dictating dictating  protected by an all-loving god  whose warm embrace  has somehow morphed into  cruel barbed wire and mace

become so fucking 
farcified
by weinstein productions
and trump corporations?
this is not
my  american dream.

text:
urgent question: what do i do, when i know of a sexual predator in the music industry...an adult male who sexually preys on underage girls? i am personally not the victim of this male musician, but several young girls have come forward to me - because they know that i know him - and they've told me their stories of being taken advantage of, and being manipulated into sex by this adult male. these girls were all underage when this happened. they've come to me looking for help. and when i confronted this alleged sexual abuser about it directly, he admitted it to me - to my face - that he did the things he was being accused of. but he'll deny it, publicly. look what happened to #christineblaseyford. look what happened to others who have come forward regarding alleged perpetrators of sexual abuse and/or sexual misconduct. remember: i was the "villain" character of a reality tv show. i will be called a liar. he and his friends will do everything they can to discredit me, if i come forward with this information. i know that this alleged predator will try to drag my name through the mud if i come forward with the information of the things he's done to underage girls. and he does have friends in the music industry. i am torn. what do i do? who do i turn to? he needs to be stopped, and he needs to be outed. you all know me as an activist. furthermore, i may be a reality tv "villain"... but i don't lie, and i have nothing to gain. and i have proof, sent to me by his alleged female victims who are too scared to come forward, themselves. what do i do? who do i turn to?  i'll take advice from anyone, at this point. thank you, all of you, in advance. please tag anyone who you think can help. ğŸ’”
@rainn @womensmarch  @voices_in_action @recordingacademy @michelinepitt @otep @regenttheaterla 
#metoo #womensrights #genderequality #womensmarch #rainn #feminism #survivor #supportsurvivors #equality #sexualassault #notalone #webelieveyou #timesup

text:
everyone talks about how awesome mom life is... but itâ€™s rare people open up about how lonely it can be. 
how so many times we lose ourselves, when we have kids. 
for a long time, i felt isolated, like i had no friends, like i was missing a part of me, like there was more of me in there, but it had been shut down. 
can you relate? 
donâ€™t get me wrong. i believe motherhood is the greatest gift!  it is the greatest blessing god could ever give. 
i love my children beyond measure. 
but, it can be lonely. 
your time, your resources all revolve around your babies. 
you skip the gym, you skip the get togethers, you skip the alone time, you let your dreams fall to the way side... and it becomes a period of mourning in the midst of joy. (weird parody i know) 
i know i am not alone. 
as i sat here reflecting on my busy- last week, i am blown away at how drastically my life has changed since launching my business. 
the massive amounts of incredible humans i have connected with, spoke with, sat down with, loved on, game planned with... that fire ğŸ”¥ is blazing brighter than it ever has. 
and the beauty is... it has made me a better mom!  a better leader.  a better friend.  a better future spouse ğŸ˜œ (1 day). mama if you feel any of this.... i get you! 
youâ€™re not alone. 
and... i would love to connect with you to give you the opportunity to learn how you no longer have to feel isolated, put yourself on the back burning and light that fire again !! â™¥ï¸

text:
warning: long post

week after week, headline after headline, of men abusing their power, money, and status to demean and objectify women is no easy thing for any woman to digest. i wish for a second these men could understand the depth of what hurt, shame, distrust, and myriad of other disturbing emotions they evoke not just in the women (lets be real, often girls) they engage with but women everywhere. 
i hope these men get the justice they deserve, either through our judicial system or karma (ğŸ™ğŸ½). god knows they deserve it. and as much as we must punish those that do wrong, we must also recognize and reward all those that do right.

thank you to all the amazing men out there. the ones who see women for more than a beautiful face, body, or sexual act. the ones who recognize and treat women as equals with love and respect. i have been blessed to meet so many of you in my life, and you remind me, not to get disheartened- good men exist â¤ï¸â¤ï¸ finally, to all the women, especially the young women, objectifying yourself... do your part. i am all for looking cute or sexy, there is nothing wrong with it, and its one of the beautiful aspects of being a woman. but be careful of the image you cultivate... you are more than just a body, you are a soul. you are multifaceted, talented, intelligent, loving, accomplished... the list goes on and on. make sure the world sees every side of you. if all you post are suggestive photos of yourself, there is a high chance, men will only think of you in one light- itâ€™s not right, but i do believe it to be true. i wish we lived in a more evolved society but unfortunately we do not yet, so please do your part. love and embrace every side of you, and donâ€™t sell yourself short as you â€œmarketâ€ yourself on social media. you deserve much better than the attention and bad juju of the creepos out there â˜ºï¸ #notokay #womenempowerment #kraft #rkelly #objectification #robertkraft #women #beingbetter #abuse #abuseofpower #men #metoo #doright #prostitution #society

text:
-Ã— afleiding Ã—-
-
het gaat even heel erg slecht. ik heb mijn psycholoog een heel heftige mail gestuurd. daardoor ben ik helemaal van slag. is de drang om mezelf iets aan te doen krankzinnig hoog. -
-
ik heb in de mail gezet dat het misschien beter is om er mee te stoppen. -
-
in mijn jonge jeugd ben ik opgenomen geweest in een ggz kliniek. omdat ik als tiener heel heftige dingen heb meegemaakt. waaronder #metoo -
-
de tijd in de kliniek is ontzettend traumatisch voor mij geweest. echt het was hel. ik was er van mijn 16e tot ongeveer mijn 17e. ik ben nu 30. ik ben hier al zo ontzettend lang mee bezig. ik krijg het niet uit mijn systeem. ik wil zo graag verder met mijn leven. maar de opname periode zorgt altijd dat mijn leven overschaduwd is. ik voel me schuldig als ik lach. ik krimp ineen als ik een compliment krijg over dat ik er goed/ leuk zie. zie je mijn dagelijkse pijn dan niet? zie je niet dat mijn ogen huilen? -
-
ik ben heel erg van mening dat deze pijn niet verder te behandelen is. dus waarom  nog therapie? ik denk dat ik met deze pijn om moet leren gaan. geen idee hoe. het is te groot. te groot om verder te behandelen. -
-

lessons learned 4 - it wasn't my fault... or was it? as i walked back to my desk, i held my mug in my hand but my fingers were shaking in anger.
.
any more than this and my coffee will spill. get a grip, girl!
.
why do men feel like they have to pass a comment about everything?
.
i went to the kitchen to make myself a cup of coffee and walked in on a group of men talking about the super bowl.
.
then i heard it - that awfully local whistle (a.k.a "cat call"), from someone with absolutely no home training or chivalry.
.
"young lady, i am sure you look into the mirror every day and thank god" "good morning sir. doesn't everybody thank god?" i replied. "but your own should be special thanks. you have very nice bodily assets that any woman would envy".
.
pin drop silence. all eyes on me.
.
i could feel them scan my body from head to toe. can the earth just open up and swallow me now!
.
i was wearing decent clothes -  a calf length skirt and loosely fitted blouse.
.
no. my button wasn't open, neither was my blouse cut low.
.
i didn't ask for this, i just wanted a cup of coffee.
.
no! it is not my fault so don't even go there.
.
or was it?
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
â€œmy name is cecibel contreras, i am a child advocate, mentor and an author. iâ€™m also the founder of it was me campaign and incest survivors united voices of america, two non-profit organizations dedicated to spreading awareness about sexual abuse and to provide support and resources for both male and female survivors that have been affected by childhood sexual abuse.

healing and recovery is a challenging process, but it is not an impossible one. you may suffer for a very long time from intrusive thoughts, flashbacks and other symptoms as a result of the sexual abuse but you must continue to press forward and walk the healing journey. i began my healing journey by sharing my story on a blogger and even though sharing my story brought a lot of pain, it also empowered me to know that i wasnâ€™t alone and that i could heal and become the rockstar that i am now.â€ cecibel from @embracing_the_beauty_in_me is a rockstar and a survivor of sexual trauma and human trafficking.Â Â read her story: https://iamarockstar.me/portfolio-items/cecibel-contreras/

text:
âœ§ flashbacks: part 4 âœ§ in the last three segments, we've learned all about flashbacks: what they are, who they affect, how they present, and the various types. now it's time to talk coping. how does one begin to combat a flashback and deliver themselves safely into the calm present? unfortunately, some of the best, failproof tools can take a lot of time to learn and require ample practice and high levels of specificity. and, whether you've just begun your healing journey or are a decade-long veteran, there are some flashbacks that make it hard to remember what's even happening to you or that skills are a thing that exist in the world. being able to call upon really detailed symptom management can be all but impossible. because of this, we wanted to compile a list of four very simple, easy-to-learn, easy-to-use skills that can help you more confidently tackle even the most disorienting flashback. and, you can use these while learning, customizing and beginning to practice the more involved skills, always knowing you have a solid foundation to rely on. you aren't helpless. you've got this.
.
ğŸŒ¿ğŸŒ³
use the link in bio or head to: beautyafterbruises.org/blog/flashbacks
ğŸŒ³ğŸŒ¿
.
we sincerely hope this "starter kit" for managing flashbacks is helpful regardless where you're at in your recovery. these tools can also be helpful for loved ones, supporters, and therapists to be well-versed in because there are times in a survivor's life where doing it alone is just too tall an order. having someone else there to walk them through can not only be exactly what they need but also be a very corrective experience.
.
we are thinking of you all and hope that your future symptoms are much less distressing and that you soon replace that feeling with one of mastery, competence and security.
.

i take no delight in seeing anyone enter the criminal justice system, because it is punitive and rarely provides rehabilitation or a second chance at life. i especially take no delight in seeing a brilliant black man go to jail.

yet, i have been triggered by the total disregard of black girls in chicago and the continued victim shaming and blaming. it relates directly to the total disregard i have felt as a black woman in america.

i am tired of feeling as if i donâ€™t matter and must constantly prove that i do. i now know it isnâ€™t just a feeling, itâ€™s an epidemic.

but today, my heart is so full!

dream hampton, and every last woman who agreed to have their stories taped are todayâ€™s black history and womenâ€™s history sheroes. kim foxx became stateâ€™s attorney and today uses her platform to bring charges that her predecessors were unable to bring.

what did they do? they advocated for themselves. they worked their way up to a level where they could affect change and then did so. 
black women. you are brilliant and deserving of protection. you must continue to advocate for yourselves. your bodies are beautiful and sacred.

when no one listens to you, persist!

#advocateforyourself #stopvictimshaming #thankyou #blackgirlmagic #metoo #sexualtrauma #rape

text:
chicago prosecutors have charged r&b star r. kelly with 10 counts of aggravated sexual abuse, according to media reports citing court records.

friday's charges come after years of allegations directed at kelly, accusing the now 52-year-old of sexual misconduct involving women and underage girls. through his lawyers, he has consistently denied them.
kelly, whose legal name is robert kelly.

jurors acquitted kelly of child pornography charges at a 2008 trial. those charges stemmed from a video prosecutors alleged showed kelly having sex with a girl as young as 13.
attorney michael avenatti said last week that he recently gave chicago prosecutors new video evidence of kelly having sex with an underage girl.

attorney michael avenatti says he has evidence r. kelly and his "enablers" paid witnesses and others to "rig" the outcome of the r&b star's 2008 trial, when he was acquitted on child pornography charges.
#timesup #metoo #rkelly predator

the news of the day is pretty wild on this friday! and makes me miss being a news reporter! *

*

2.) r. kelly charged with 10 felony counts of sexual assault against 4 teenage girls.
